generated_description:  This painting, "Die Schwalben sammeln sich" by Max Pechstein, reflects the Expressionist movement, which emerged in the early 20th century, emphasizing emotional and subjective experience over realistic representation. The vibrant colors and distorted forms capture the artist's emotional state during the post-World War II era, reflecting the turmoil and introspection of the time. The presence of a windmill adds a rural, nostalgic element, contrasting with the modernity suggested by the power lines.
